cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG

The paper deals with generating 3D human pose hypotheses from 2D joint detections in RGB images, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves generating diverse and valid pose hypotheses, which could fall under the category of graphics (cs.GR). The use of a generative model and anatomical constraints suggests that the paper could also be relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper's focus on generating diverse hypotheses could also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG).
